This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the interpretation of deep neural networks. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as DNNs are a popular tool in AI research. The paper also mentions the use of semantic concepts in computer vision tasks, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Furthermore, the paper discusses the interpretation of local behaviors, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) as it deals with understanding individual decisions made by DNNs. Finally, the paper's focus on optimization problems and mathematical formulations suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
